President Donald Trump hosted President Moon Jae-in of South Korea at the White House to strengthen the strategic alliance between the two countries and address the threat posed by North Korea. They reaffirmed the commitment of the United States to defend South Korea against any attack and pledged to enhance the mutual security and defense capabilities of the alliance. Both leaders called on North Korea to cease its provocative actions and fulfill its international obligations. They also discussed promoting regional relations and trilateral cooperation with Japan, advancing fair trade, enhancing bilateral economic cooperation, and collaborating as global partners on issues such as global health security and the fight against ISIS. The leaders emphasized the importance of the United States-ROK alliance and expressed their expectation for its continued growth and strengthening. President Moon invited President Trump to visit South Korea in 2017, which was accepted.